--- CoreAI Git Tracking Configuration ---
Ignore the heavy raw database (Wont be uploaded to GitHub)
coreai_vault.db
coreai_vault.db-journal
Keep the compressed database! (This WILL be uploaded to GitHub)
!coreai_vault.zip
Ignore local run progress files and logs
ingest_progress.json
*.log
build_log.txt
check_db.log
Ignore local Python runtime caching
pycache/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
venv/
.env
Ignore environment/IDE configurations
.vscode/
.DS_Store
This will generate a highly compressed ⁠coreai_vault.zip⁠ file in your folder that easily fits within GitHub's limits!
Step 2: Integrate the Unpacker into ⁠app.py⁠
Open your ⁠app.py⁠ file in VS Code and import the helper at the very top of your script (above your database connections):
Save your ⁠app.py⁠ file (⁠Ctrl + S⁠).
Step 3: Push Your Clean App to GitHub
Open your terminal and run the git push sequence:
(Because of our custom ⁠.gitignore⁠, Git will ignore the large ⁠coreai_vault.db⁠ file and safely track ⁠coreai_vault.zip⁠ instead!)
Link your online GitHub repository and push your code:

